journal.description.minecraft.cod: A staple of colder seas. These fish are known for their calm presence under the waves.
journal.description.minecraft.pufferfish: Their survival tactics are quite simple. If anyone gets close, blow up.
journal.description.minecraft.salmon: This strong and resilient fish is a familiar face for all anglers (and a tasty snack).
journal.description.minecraft.tropical_f: One of the most diverse and vibrant fish in the sea, with over 3,000 recorded varieties.
journal.description.tide.abyss_angler: Its lure shines especially bright, allowing it to thrive even deeper than its cousins.
journal.description.tide.alpha_fish: Driven to near extinction by other fish, this familiar-looking species wanders the depths of the overworld.
journal.description.tide.amber_rockfish: This fish is literally made out of rock, with bright orange moss covering its body.
journal.description.tide.anchovy: These tiny fish move in large schools that swirl through oceans, creating dynamic patterns.
journal.description.tide.angelfish: Brightly colored and graceful, often found elegantly gliding through coral reefs.
journal.description.tide.anglerfish: The bright lure on this fish's head attracts food, allowing them to conserve energy while they hunt.
journal.description.tide.aquathorn: A much less aggressive (and smaller) ancestor of the guardians of undersea monuments.
journal.description.tide.arapaima: This giant creature glides through warm jungle rivers with strength and speed.
journal.description.tide.ash_perch: This fish lurks in the depths of lava lakes, traveling quickly and blending seamlessly with its fiery surroundings.
journal.description.tide.bedrock_bug: Its teeth can penetrate bedrock, allowing them to build nests in the depths of the overworld.
journal.description.tide.bedrock_tetra: This tiny fish is concealed beneath a solid layer of bedrock, rendering it impervious to predators.
journal.description.tide.black_crappie: Dark and patterned, the black crappie thrives in clear lakes and puts up a fight.
journal.description.tide.blazing_swordfi: This swordfish has shimmering scales, a razor-sharp nose, and can be used as a deadly weapon.
journal.description.tide.blossom_bass: A bright and colorful catch among the cherry blossoms. They radiate with a calming power.
journal.description.tide.blue_neonfish: This fish has a set of dark, jagged teeth that bite through even the toughest scales.
journal.description.tide.bluegill: A classic catch in calm ponds and lakes of any region. They're always hungry for some bait.
journal.description.tide.brook_trout: Smaller and more secretive than other trout, the brook trout favors shaded streams and mossy pools.
journal.description.tide.bull_shark: A powerful swimmer with a short temper, notably able to travel upriver to freshwater environments.
journal.description.tide.carp: This bottom-feeder thrives in murky waters and often stirs up a mess in its search for food.
journal.description.tide.catfish: This fish has whiskered jaws and a taste for the night. Rumors say it fears the presence of wolves.
journal.description.tide.cave_crawler: This unique quadruped is quick on its feet and can scale any surface.
journal.description.tide.cave_eel: These little cave noodles can fit between thin gaps in rocky terrain to search for food.
journal.description.tide.chasm_eel: This gulper eel is incredibly resilient. It feasts on pieces of bedrock lying in the deepest depths.
journal.description.tide.chorus_cod: This fish seems to have formed a strange relationship with a chorus flower, providing it with free food.
journal.description.tide.coelacanth: A living fossil, thought to be extinct for millions of years. They lurk in dark caves to avoid light.
journal.description.tide.crimson_fangjaw: This creature evolved to be a powerful hunter in its hostile home. Its diet seems to consist of...pork?
journal.description.tide.crystal_shrimp: The origins of this specimen are unknown. It sparkles and shines as it drifts through aquifers.
journal.description.tide.crystalline_car: The makeup of the crystals surrounding this mysterious fish's scales is unknown.
journal.description.tide.darkness_eater: Legend says that this massive catfish can swallow five iron golems with one bite.
journal.description.tide.deep_blue: This fish's tough skin and versatile diet allow it to survive much longer than other fish.
journal.description.tide.deep_grouper: Its pale, dark reddish-black scales give this fish an otherworldly look.
journal.description.tide.devils_hole_pup: Tiny and iridescent, it hides in one of the most isolated and extreme aquatic habitats.
journal.description.tide.dragon_fish: Legend speaks of a player who submerged a dragon egg in water for several years, eventually creating this.
journal.description.tide.dripstone_darte: Is it a stalagmite, or a stalactite? Either way, its pointy nose is useful for hunting.
journal.description.tide.dutchman_sock: This species of bacteria grows so large that it's often mistaken for a fish (or a sock).
journal.description.tide.echo_snapper: Some sculk surrounding a lifeless fish bone. Even so, it feels like it's listening for something.
journal.description.tide.elytrout: An elegant bug-like creature that resembles the same elytra found in ancient end cities.
journal.description.tide.ember_koi: These fish are at the bottom of the food chain, but can use the lava itself to create more of them.
journal.description.tide.ender_glider: A winged alien fish, able to traverse the end much more quickly than the rest.
journal.description.tide.enderfin: This fish's metallic skin is covered in a deep blue hue, giving it a pearl-like appearance.
journal.description.tide.endergazer: This fish has a large eye that makes up its head. In addition to providing sight, the eye also serves as a brain.
journal.description.tide.flounder: These uniquely-shaped fish rest flat against sandy or muddy sea floors, staying hidden from predators.
journal.description.tide.frostbite_floun: A flounder that seems to be frozen in place. They lurk on chilly seafloors.
journal.description.tide.gilded_minnow: This fish is said to have been the victim of a much more powerful creature, turning its scales golden.
journal.description.tide.glowfish: A bioluminescent fish that lives peacefully in the depths. They're said to be distant relatives of squids.
journal.description.tide.great_white_sha: A feared and respected predator, patrolling coastal waters with keen senses and bursts of speed.
journal.description.tide.guppy: This fish is tiny, colorful, and endlessly active. It thrives in warm and tropical waters.
journal.description.tide.incandescent_la: Its transparent skin helps it glow with its own body heat. A tasty snack for many fish.
journal.description.tide.inferno_guppy: This tiny fish absorbs large amounts of energy from lava, completely eliminating the need for food.
journal.description.tide.iron_tetra: This fish lurks around ore veins building up a metallic frame, keeping it safe from most predators.
journal.description.tide.judgment_fish: Its big eyes allow it to see predators clearly and make a move before they get close.
journal.description.tide.lapis_lanternfi: This tiny lapis lazuli fish possesses shocking amounts of strength and speed.
journal.description.tide.largemouth_bass: A bold and aggressive predator. This lake-dwelling fish is a widely-accepted favorite.
journal.description.tide.luminescent_jel: This peaceful jellyfish's bright light helps guide other fish living in the depths.
journal.description.tide.mackerel: Fast-moving, tightly schooling, and a common sight in coastal waters and open seas.
journal.description.tide.magma_mackerel: With heat resistant scales and powerful fins, this tiny fish navigates lava pools with ease.
journal.description.tide.mahi_mahi: These long fish have dazzling colors and a blunt, rounded head.
journal.description.tide.manta_ray: Its wide fins carry it gracefully through open water near the surface of warm seas.
journal.description.tide.mantyvern: This surprisingly docile creature creates signals with its antennae for communication.
journal.description.tide.marstilus: This dusty nautilus-like creature's qualities are unlike anything found in the overworld.
journal.description.tide.midas_fish: A fish blessed with the ability to turn things into gold. Unfortunately for the fish, it can no longer eat its prey.
journal.description.tide.mirage_catfish: Found under extreme heat, this catfish has confused travelers for many years.
journal.description.tide.mooneye: Few have spotted this fish in the wild. They thrive in cool waters yet remain hidden from sight.
journal.description.tide.nephrosilu: This deformed abomination is an apex predator, with razor-sharp fins and a bright purple eye.
journal.description.tide.neptune_koi: This fish has beautiful glowing rings around its body. Rumors say that it protects waters from evil spirits.
journal.description.tide.obsidian_pike: Researchers can't figure out how this pike can even move its fins with its rock-hard composition.
journal.description.tide.ocean_perch: This perch is often found schooling near rocky seafloors and cold ocean depths.
journal.description.tide.pale_clubfish: These oddly shaped fish are surprisingly common and are a tasty snack for predators and anglers.
journal.description.tide.pentapus: This slimy, translucent purple creature has five legs. Is its center body part an eye or a brain?
journal.description.tide.pike: Long, lean, and carnivorous, these fish rule small lakes and ambush prey with their speed.
journal.description.tide.pluto_snail: Crawling at the bottom of the ocean, this colorful snail is much less sluggish than its relatives.
journal.description.tide.rainbow_trout: With their vibrant colors, these fish are common sights in cool rivers and streams.
journal.description.tide.red_40: This eyeless insect is surprisingly quick, moving through either water or the void with ease.
journal.description.tide.red_snapper: Known for its vibrant red hue, it inhabits rocky bottoms in coastal waters.
journal.description.tide.sailfish: Known for its impressive dorsal fin, it speeds through open oceans hunting fish with quick strikes.
journal.description.tide.sand_tiger_shar: With jagged teeth and a menacing appearance, they search the desert for prey.
journal.description.tide.saturn_cuttlefi: This pale-colored cuttlefish has a distinctive ring orbiting its head.
journal.description.tide.shadow_shark: This spooky predator possesses absurdly sharp teeth but relatively weak skin.
journal.description.tide.shadow_snapper: A stealthy predator of the deep that strikes swiftly with its razor-sharp teeth.
journal.description.tide.shooting_starfi: Some anglers talk about fish that fall from the sky. Looks like they were onto something.
journal.description.tide.sleepy_carp: A lazy, passive fish that spends most of its time sitting in one spot.
journal.description.tide.slimy_salmon: A bouncy shell of a fish made out of slime. Its covering allows it to withstand almost anything.
journal.description.tide.smallmouth_bass: A lookalike to their large-mouthed cousins, these fish prefer slightly cooler and calmer waters.
journal.description.tide.snatcher_squid: This squid routinely travels to the pressurized death zone of the void, dragging its prey with it.
journal.description.tide.snook: This fish is a common sight in coastal waters, being able to tolerate many different habitats.
journal.description.tide.soulscale: This fish is woven out of strands of soul soil possessed by a ghostly spirit.
journal.description.tide.spore_stalker: This fungal fiend flocks to nearby mushrooms. It's possible that it may have been a fish at some point.
journal.description.tide.sturgeon: A bottom-feeding fish with tough scales and a long snout. They cruise the depths of cold rivers and lakes.
journal.description.tide.sun_emblem: A luminous jellyfish with a spiky shell to protect itself from harm.
journal.description.tide.swordfish: A powerful predator with a long, flat bill used to slash prey. It cruises deep waters in search of food.
journal.description.tide.tuna: Built for speed and endurance, this open-ocean predator can travel vast distances.
journal.description.tide.uranias_pisces: Many anglers believe that this fish is from heaven itself. It's said to bring good fortune to whomever catches it.
journal.description.tide.vengeance: Is it a ghost? Is it a fish? Regardless, it's highly territorial and aggressive towards anything.
journal.description.tide.violet_carp: Many have debated where this carp gets its unique colors from. Still, no one knows.
journal.description.tide.voidseeker: Not much is known about the voidseeker, except that they hop between dimensions to avoid getting caught.
journal.description.tide.volcano_tuna: This fish is able to live for up to 600 years before becoming enveloped in obsidian and sinking to the floor.
journal.description.tide.walleye: Lurking in the chilly depths, this sharp-eyed fish is prized by many anglers.
journal.description.tide.warped_guppy: Protected by heat-resistant hyphae, this fungal fellow travels through lava oceans far beyond its home biome.
journal.description.tide.white_crappie: This light-colored fish favors slower waters and is a common recreational catch.
journal.description.tide.windbass: This fish possesses incredible speed, powered by its ability to create wind currents beneath the water.
journal.description.tide.witherfin: Once a thriving creature, it now holds a deadly infection that is passed to those who touch it.
journal.description.tide.yellow_perch: This bright yellow-striped fish is as eye-catching as it is abundant.

text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.ambi: Enables the ripple effects on the fishable void surface
text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.crat: The amount that the crate chance is scaled with higher fishing luck (see wiki for more info)
The chance of a crate being selected from the fishing loot table (not a percent, see wiki for more info)
text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.defa: Enable this to use the default black fishing line color
text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.fish: A list that defines the fishable void heights for each dimension
text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.hold: When enabled, you can hold right-click to cast the bobber farther
text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.logD: For datapackers: enable to show Tide data loading errors in the logs
text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.over: When enabled, the vanilla fishing rod will use Tide's fishing loot system
text.autoconfig.tide.option.general.rodD: Multiplier applied to the durability of fishing rods
text.autoconfig.tide.option.items.bucket: Controls when fish items should be bucketable via menus
text.autoconfig.tide.option.items.fishIt: The following only applies if Bucketable Fish Items is set to "Only When Living"
The duration, in seconds, of how long a fish item is bucketable after being caught

Note: If Fish Item Sizes is set to "Always" or Bucketable Fish Items is set to "While Living", extra data will be added to fish item stacks that make them unstackable.
To make fish stackable, simply change both settings to something other than their defaults.
Controls when/where fish should be assigned a length
text.autoconfig.tide.option.journal.give: Give players a fishing journal upon joining a world for the first time
text.autoconfig.tide.option.journal.show: Shows a notification (toast) that appears when a new fish is discovered
Highlight fish icons in yellow until you click on them for the first time
text.autoconfig.tide.option.journal.useA: Disable to use 24-hour time in the journal and pocket watches (ex. 21:00 vs 9:00 PM)
text.autoconfig.tide.option.journal.useF: Enable to use Fahrenheit instead of Celsius in the journal and thermometers (ex. 0C vs 32F)
text.autoconfig.tide.option.journal.useR: If enabled, the real date is used in the fishing journal as opposed to the local world day
text.autoconfig.tide.option.minigame.doF: Enables the sound played when you lose the minigame
Enables scoring messages after a minigame (ex. Perfect Catch!)
text.autoconfig.tide.option.minigame.doS: Enables the sound played when you win the minigame
text.autoconfig.tide.option.minigame.min: A multiplier that increases or decreases the speed of the minigame
text.autoconfig.tide.title: Tide Config
text.tide.rod_tooltip.crystal_bonus: Plays sound when a fish bites
